dlinkSwDhcp6ServerMIB.name: dlinkSwDhcp6ServerMIB

revisions.description: This is the first version of the MIB file for 'DHCPv6 Server' functionality.
modify node dDhcp6SBindExpire syntax to DateAndTime.

dlinkSwDhcp6ServerMIB.contactinfo: D-Link Corporation Postal: No. 289, Sinhu 3rd Rd., Neihu District, Taipei City 114, Taiwan, R.O.C Tel: +886-2-66000123 E-mail: tsd@dlink.com.tw
dlinkSwDhcp6ServerMIB.description: This MIB module defines objects for DHCPv6 Server.

dDhcp6ServiceEnabled.name: dDhcp6ServiceEnabled
dDhcp6ServiceEnabled.description: This object enables/disables the DHCPv6 server and relay service on the device.

dDhcp6SCfgChanged.name: dDhcp6SCfgChanged
dDhcp6SCfgChanged.description: The configuration changes of DHCPv6 server cannot take effect on-the-fly. This ojbect indicates whether the DHCPv6 server configuration has changed since the DHCPv6 service was enabled.

dDhcp6SExcludedAddressTable.name: dDhcp6SExcludedAddressTable
dDhcp6SExcludedAddressTable.description: A list of configurations about a range of IPv6 addresses that the DHCPv6 server should not assign to DHCPv6 client.

dDhcp6SExcludedAddressEntry.name: dDhcp6SExcludedAddressEntry
dDhcp6SExcludedAddressEntry.description: An entry contans information about an IP address range that the DHCPv6 server should not assign to DHCPv6 client.

dDhcp6SExcludedAddressBeginAddr.name: dDhcp6SExcludedAddressBeginAddr
dDhcp6SExcludedAddressBeginAddr.description: This object indicates the first IPv6 address of this excluded address range.

dDhcp6SExcludedAddressEndAddr.name: dDhcp6SExcludedAddressEndAddr
dDhcp6SExcludedAddressEndAddr.description: This object indicates the last IPv6 address of this excluded address range.

dDhcp6SExcludedAddressRowStatus.name: dDhcp6SExcludedAddressRowStatus
dDhcp6SExcludedAddressRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dDhcp6SLocalPoolTable.name: dDhcp6SLocalPoolTable
dDhcp6SLocalPoolTable.description: A list of configurations contains information for local IPv6 prefix pools.

dDhcp6SLocalPoolEntry.name: dDhcp6SLocalPoolEntry
dDhcp6SLocalPoolEntry.description: An entry contains information about a local IPv6 prefix pool that will be assigned to DHCPv6 client.

dDhcp6SLocalPoolName.name: dDhcp6SLocalPoolName
dDhcp6SLocalPoolName.description: The name of this local IPv6 prefix pool.

dDhcp6SLocalPoolPrefix.name: dDhcp6SLocalPoolPrefix
dDhcp6SLocalPoolPrefix.description: This object indicates the IPv6 prefix address of the local pool.

dDhcp6SLocalPoolPrefixLen.name: dDhcp6SLocalPoolPrefixLen
dDhcp6SLocalPoolPrefixLen.description: This object indicates the IPv6 prefix length in bits of the local pool.

dDhcp6SLocalPoolPrefixAssignLen.name: dDhcp6SLocalPoolPrefixAssignLen
dDhcp6SLocalPoolPrefixAssignLen.description: This object indicates the prefix length in bits to delegate to DHCPv6 client from the pool. The value of dDhcp6SLocalPoolPrefixAssignLen cannot be less than the value of dDhcp6SLocalPoolPrefixLen.

dDhcp6SLocalPoolFreeAddrNum.name: dDhcp6SLocalPoolFreeAddrNum
dDhcp6SLocalPoolFreeAddrNum.description: This object indicates the number of prefixes which are available to be allocated.

dDhcp6SLocalPoolInUseAddrNum.name: dDhcp6SLocalPoolInUseAddrNum
dDhcp6SLocalPoolInUseAddrNum.description: This object indicates the number of already allocated prefixes.

dDhcp6SLocalPoolRowStatus.name: dDhcp6SLocalPoolRowStatus
dDhcp6SLocalPoolRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dDhcp6SPoolTable.name: dDhcp6SPoolTable
dDhcp6SPoolTable.description: A table of DHCPv6 pool Information.

dDhcp6SPoolEntry.name: dDhcp6SPoolEntry
dDhcp6SPoolEntry.description: Defines an entry in the dDhcp6SPoolTable.

dDhcp6SPoolRowStatus.name: dDhcp6SPoolRowStatus
dDhcp6SPoolRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows.

dDhcp6SPoolDomainNameTable.name: dDhcp6SPoolDomainNameTable
dDhcp6SPoolDomainNameTable.description: A table of domain name information in DHCPv6 pools.

dDhcp6SPoolDomainNameEntry.name: dDhcp6SPoolDomainNameEntry
dDhcp6SPoolDomainNameEntry.description: Defines an entry in the dDhcp6SPoolDomainNameTable. The first instance identifier index value identifies the dDhcp6SPoolEntry that a domain name (dDhcp6SPoolDomainNameEntry) belongs to. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding dDhcp6SPoolEntry is deleted.

dDhcp6SPoolDomainNameAdminIndex.name: dDhcp6SPoolDomainNameAdminIndex
dDhcp6SPoolDomainNameAdminIndex.description: This object indicates the order of preference of a domain name in a DHCPv6 pool. The number of domain name can be specified in a DHCPv6 pool is project dependent.

dDhcp6SPoolDomainName.name: dDhcp6SPoolDomainName
dDhcp6SPoolDomainName.description: The domain name of the corresponding entry.

dhcp6ServerDomainNameRowStatus.name: dhcp6ServerDomainNameRowStatus
dhcp6ServerDomainNameRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows.

dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerTable.name: dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerTable
dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerTable.description: A list of DNS server configurations for DHCPv6 pools.

dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerEntry.name: dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerEntry
dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerEntry.description: An entry contains DNS server configuration in a DHCPv6 pool. The first instance identifier index value identifies the dDhcp6SPoolEntry that a DNS server (dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerEntry) belongs to. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding dDhcp6SPoolEntry is deleted.

dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerIndex.name: dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerIndex
dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerIndex.description: This objects indicates the order of preference of a DNS server in a DHCPv6 pool.

dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerAddr.name: dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerAddr
dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerAddr.description: The IPv6 address of the DNS server.

dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerRowStatus.name: dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerRowStatus
dDhcp6SPoolDnsServerRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixTable.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixTable
dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixTable.description: A table of address prefix information in DHCPv6 pools.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixEntry.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixEntry
dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixEntry.description: Defines an entry in the dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixTable. The first instance identifier index value identifies the dDhcp6SPoolEntry that a address-prefix (dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixEntry) belongs to. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding dDhcp6SPoolEntry is deleted.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixAddr.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixAddr
dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixAddr.description: This object indicates IPv6 address prefix to be assigned to client.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixLength.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixLength
dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixLength.description: This object indicates the length in bits of the address prefix.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixVLtime.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixVLtime
dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixVLtime.description: The valid lifetime of the address prefix in seconds.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixPLtime.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixPLtime
dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixPLtime.description: The preferred lifetime of the address prefix in seconds.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixRowStatus.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixRowStatus
dDhcp6SPoolAddrPrefixRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignTable.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignTable
dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignTable.description: A table of address assignment information in DHCPv6 pools.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignEntry.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignEntry
dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignEntry.description: Defines an entry in the dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignTable. The first instance identifier index value identifies the dDhcp6SPoolEntry that an address-assignment (dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignEntry) belongs to. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding dDhcp6SPoolEntry is deleted.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignAddr.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignAddr
dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignAddr.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address to be assigned to client.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignLength.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignLength
dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignLength.description: This object indicates the length in bits of the address.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignClientDuid.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignClientDuid
dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignClientDuid.description: This object indicates the DHCP unique identifier (DUID) of the client to get the address.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignSetIaid.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignSetIaid
dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignSetIaid.description: This object indicates whether dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignIaid is set or not.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignIaid.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignIaid
dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignIaid.description: This object indicates the Identity association identifier (IAID) of the entry. The value of dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignIaid uniquely identifies a collection of non-temporary addresses (IA_NA) assigned on the client. dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignIaid is only valid when dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignSetIaid is 'true'.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignVLtime.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignVLtime
dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignVLtime.description: This object indicates valid lifetime of the assigned address in seconds. The valid lifetime should be greater than preferred lifetime.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignPLtime.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignPLtime
dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignPLtime.description: This object indicates preferred lifetime of the assigned address in seconds. The valid lifetime should be greater than preferred lifetime.

dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignRowStatus.name: dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignRowStatus
dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows.

dDhcp6SPoolPdTable.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdTable
dDhcp6SPoolPdTable.description: A table of prefix delegation information in DHCPv6 pools.

dDhcp6SPoolPdEntry.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdEntry
dDhcp6SPoolPdEntry.description: Defines an entry in the dDhcp6SPoolPdTable. The first instance identifier index value identifies the dDhcp6SPoolEntry that a prefix delegation (dDhcp6SPoolPdEntry) belongs to. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding dDhcp6SPoolEntry is deleted.

dDhcp6SPoolPdPrefix.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdPrefix
dDhcp6SPoolPdPrefix.description: This object indicates IPv6 prefix to be delegated to client.

dDhcp6SPoolPdPrefixLength.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdPrefixLength
dDhcp6SPoolPdPrefixLength.description: This object indicates the length in bits of the prefix.

dDhcp6SPoolPdClientDuid.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdClientDuid
dDhcp6SPoolPdClientDuid.description: This object indicates the DHCP unique identifier (DUID) of the client to get the address.

dDhcp6SPoolPdSetIaid.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdSetIaid
dDhcp6SPoolPdSetIaid.description: This object indicates whether dDhcp6SPoolPdIaid is set or not.

dDhcp6SPoolPdIaid.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdIaid
dDhcp6SPoolPdIaid.description: This object indicates the Identity association identifier (IAID) of the entry. The value of dDhcp6SPoolPdIaid uniquely identifies a collection of prefixes assigned to the requesting router. dDhcp6SPoolPdIaid is only valid when dDhcp6SPoolAddrAssignSetIaid is 'true'.

dDhcp6SPoolPdVLtime.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdVLtime
dDhcp6SPoolPdVLtime.description: This object indicates valid lifetime of the allocated prefix in seconds. The valid lifetime should be greater than preferred lifetime.

dDhcp6SPoolPdPLtime.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdPLtime
dDhcp6SPoolPdPLtime.description: This object indicates preferred lifetime of the address in seconds. The preferred lifetime should be less than valid lifetime.

dDhcp6SPoolPdRowStatus.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdRowStatus
dDhcp6SPoolPdRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows.

dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolTable.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolTable
dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolTable.description: A table of local prefix pool association in DHCPv6 pools.

dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolEntry.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolEntry
dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolEntry.description: Defines an entry in the dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolTable. The first instance identifier index value identifies the dDhcp6SPoolEntry that a local prefix pool association (dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolEntry) belongs to. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding dDhcp6SPoolEntry is deleted.

dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolName.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolName
dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolName.description: The name of the associated local IPv6 prefix pool.

dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolVLtime.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolVLtime
dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolVLtime.description: This object indicates valid lifetime for the delegated prefix in seconds. The valid lifetime should be greater than preferred lifetime.

dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolPLtime.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolPLtime
dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolPLtime.description: This object indicates preferred lifetime for the delegated prefix in seconds. The preferred lifetime should be less than valid lifetime.

dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolRowStatus.name: dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolRowStatus
dDhcp6SPoolPdLocPoolRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows.

dDhcp6ServIfTable.name: dDhcp6ServIfTable
dDhcp6ServIfTable.description: A table contains interface-specific DHCPv6 server service configuration. An entry is created/removed when DHCPv6 server service is specified/unspecified. When DHCPv6 server service is specified on an interface means DHCPv6 server feature is enabled on that interface.

dDhcp6ServIfEntry.name: dDhcp6ServIfEntry
dDhcp6ServIfEntry.description: Defines an entry in the dDhcp6ServIfTable.

dDhcp6ServIfIndex.name: dDhcp6ServIfIndex
dDhcp6ServIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface. Only VLAN interfaces are valid interfaces.

dDhcp6ServIfPoolName.name: dDhcp6ServIfPoolName
dDhcp6ServIfPoolName.description: This object indicates the name of the DHCPv6 pool used to serve the request received on the interface.

dDhcp6ServIfRapidCommit.name: dDhcp6ServIfRapidCommit
dDhcp6ServIfRapidCommit.description: This object indicates whether allow proceeding of two-message exchange.

dDhcp6ServIfAllowHint.name: dDhcp6ServIfAllowHint
dDhcp6ServIfAllowHint.description: This object indicates whether delegate the prefix based on the prefix hint by the client. By default, the prefix hint by client is ignored.

dDhcp6ServIfPreference.name: dDhcp6ServIfPreference
dDhcp6ServIfPreference.description: This object indicates the preference value to be advertised by the server. The larger value indicates the higher priority.

dDhcp6ServIfRowStatus.name: dDhcp6ServIfRowStatus
dDhcp6ServIfRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows.

dDhcp6SBindingTable.name: dDhcp6SBindingTable
dDhcp6SBindingTable.description: A table contains DHCPv6 binding information.

dDhcp6SBindingEntry.name: dDhcp6SBindingEntry
dDhcp6SBindingEntry.description: Defines an entry in the dDhcp6SBindingTable.

dDhcp6SBindIfIndex.name: dDhcp6SBindIfIndex
dDhcp6SBindIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the VLAN interface on which the binding is located.

dDhcp6SBindClientDuid.name: dDhcp6SBindClientDuid
dDhcp6SBindClientDuid.description: This object indicates the DHCP unique identifier (DUID) of the client.

dDhcp6SBindIaType.name: dDhcp6SBindIaType
dDhcp6SBindIaType.description: The type of binding IA (Identity association). other(0) - The other types not specified here. iapd(1) - Prefix Delegation iana(2) - Non-temporary Addresses

dDhcp6SBindIaId.name: dDhcp6SBindIaId
dDhcp6SBindIaId.description: This object indicates the Identity association identifier (IAID) of the entry.

dDhcp6SBindAddrOrPrefix.name: dDhcp6SBindAddrOrPrefix
dDhcp6SBindAddrOrPrefix.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address or prefix allocated to the client.

dDhcp6SBindAddrOrPrefixLen.name: dDhcp6SBindAddrOrPrefixLen
dDhcp6SBindAddrOrPrefixLen.description: This object indicates the length in bits of the IPv6 address or prefix allocated/delegated to the client.

dDhcp6SBindClientLinkLocalAddr.name: dDhcp6SBindClientLinkLocalAddr
dDhcp6SBindClientLinkLocalAddr.description: This object indicates the IPv6 link local address or prefix allocated/delegated to the client.

dDhcp6SBindIaT1.name: dDhcp6SBindIaT1
dDhcp6SBindIaT1.description: This object indicates T1 of the IA. At time T1 for an IA, the client initiates a Renew/Reply message exchange to extend the lifetimes on any addresses in the IA.

dDhcp6SBindIaT2.name: dDhcp6SBindIaT2
dDhcp6SBindIaT2.description: This object indicates T2 of the IA. At time T2 for an IA, the client initiates a Rebind/Reply message exchange with any available server.

dDhcp6SBindVLtime.name: dDhcp6SBindVLtime
dDhcp6SBindVLtime.description: This object indicates valid lifetime for the binding in seconds.

dDhcp6SBindPLtime.name: dDhcp6SBindPLtime
dDhcp6SBindPLtime.description: This object indicates preferred lifetime for the binding in seconds.

dDhcp6SBindExpire.name: dDhcp6SBindExpire
dDhcp6SBindExpire.description: This object indicates the expiration of the binding entry. The special value of all '00'Hs indicates that the binding will never be expired (infinite).

dDhcp6SBindClear.name: dDhcp6SBindClear
dDhcp6SBindClear.description: This object is used to clear the binding entry when set to 'clear'. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noOp'. When read, the value 'noOp' is returned.

dDhcp6ServerCompliance.name: dDhcp6ServerCompliance
dDhcp6ServerCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the DLINKSW-DHCP6-SERVER-MIB.

dDhcp6SGblCfgGroup.name: dDhcp6SGblCfgGroup
dDhcp6SGblCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects providing global configuration about DHCPv6 server.

dDhcp6SLocalPoolGroup.name: dDhcp6SLocalPoolGroup
dDhcp6SLocalPoolGroup.description: A collection of objects providing DHCP class configuration.

dDhcp6SPoolGroup.name: dDhcp6SPoolGroup
dDhcp6SPoolGroup.description: A collection of objects providing DHCP relay agent configuration of a class or address range of a class under a DHCP pool.

dDhcp6SInterfaceGroup.name: dDhcp6SInterfaceGroup
dDhcp6SInterfaceGroup.description: A collection of objects providing interface-specific configuration for DHCPv6 Server feature.

dDhcp6SNonTempAddrAssignGroup.name: dDhcp6SNonTempAddrAssignGroup
dDhcp6SNonTempAddrAssignGroup.description: A collection of objects providing non-temporary addresses configuration for DHCPv6 Server feature.

dDhcp6SPrefixDelegationGroup.name: dDhcp6SPrefixDelegationGroup
dDhcp6SPrefixDelegationGroup.description: A collection of objects providing prefix-delegation configuration for DHCPv6 Server feature.

dDhcp6SInfoGroup.name: dDhcp6SInfoGroup
dDhcp6SInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects providing dynamic information for DHCPv6 Server feature.
